Review: this is a well made, albeit very confusing movie. you can never tell if it wants to be a straight up comedy, a satire, or a dramatic religious epic and in the confusion it sort of all falls short. it works best as the latter even though it can never really overcome the problems of the uneven script. it looks absolutely gorgeous and you can tell jeymes samuel has a great eye, i just think the rest of the skills…

everything about this works until it ends on such a cynical, almost painfully dour note. all four performances are wonderful, but andrew scott is operating on such an insanely different level. he’s asked to do the impossible in this and he is so successful. i think i will grow to love this movie a lot more with time, because the parts that work are so fantastic, i just wish it left us with a little bit of optimism for the main character going forward. ah, the movies
